{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"@"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Video"},{"kind":"text","text":"(...)"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":[null]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"source","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The name and file extension of a video in your Swift framework or package project. "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(required)"}]}]}]},{"name":"poster","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The name and file extension of an image in your Swift framework or package project. This image serves as a poster image for the video and shows when the video isn’t playing. "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(required)"}]}]}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Video"},{"type":"text","text":" directive displays a video in your tutorial. Provide the name of a video and the name of a poster image to show when the video isn’t playing."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"markdown","code":["@Video(source: \"sloth-smiling.mp4\", poster: \"happy-sloth-frame.png\")"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Videos and poster images can exist anywhere in your code base, but it’s good practice to centralize them in a resources folder. You create a resources` folder in your documentation catalog."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Within your code base, media file names must be unique. Videos must be in "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":".mov"}]},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":".mp4"}]},{"type":"text","text":" format. Poster images must be in "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineCo